'''女性凝视'''/'''女性视角'''（{{lang-en|female gaze}}），在[[女性主义理论|女性主义理论]]中，女性凝视指在[[視覺藝術|视觉艺术]]<ref>{{cite encyclopedia|url=http://plato.stanford.edu/entries/feminism-aesthetics/|title=Feminist Aesthetics|encyclopedia=Stanford Encyclopedia of Philosophy|quote=Assumes a standard point of view that is masculine and heterosexual. . . . The phrase 'male gaze' refers to the frequent framing of objects of visual art so that the viewer is situated in a masculine position of appreciation.|date=Winter 2012|access-date=13 May 2015|archive-date=2019-08-02|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20190802101040/https://plato.stanford.edu/entries/feminism-aesthetics/|dead-url=no}}</ref>和在[[文學|文学创作]]<ref>That the male gaze applies to literature and to the visual arts: Łuczyńska-Hołdys, Małgorzata (2013). ''Soft-Shed Kisses: Re-visioning the Femme Fatale in English Poetry of the 19th Century'', Cambridge Scholars Publishing, p. 15.</ref>中，从[[女异性恋者|女异性恋者]]的角度描绘[[男性|男性]]和[[現實|现实]]，将男性[[性客体化|性客体化]]以取悦异性恋女性观众的行为<ref>{{cite journal|last=Eaton|first=E.W.|title=Feminist Philosophy of Art|journal= Philosophy Compass|volume=3|issue=5|pages=873–893 |publisher=Wiley-Blackwell|doi=10.1111/j.1747-9991.2008.00154.x|date=September 2008}}</ref>。

